table-1339-679.pgTitle: List of Baa Bahoo Aur Baby episodes
table-1339-679.caption: Episodes 1–511
data: Thakkar family is introduced while celebrating Baby's birthday
Baby gets angry on Baa when she forbids her to go on a trip with her friends
Baby gets lost and falls unconscious when she goes shopping with her family
The Thakkar family search desperately for Baby and call the police
A man named Anish saves Baby and the family thanks him
Dimple taunts Anish for ruining her scarf. Baby challenges to Dimple and decides to earn money on her own.
Baby asks Arvind about him reason behind hating her father. The family members suggest jobs for Baby, but she is unsuccessful.
Baa taunts Meenakshi for drinking alcohol. Baa catches Baby and Gattu selling liquor samples on Anish's request, without informing her
Meenakshi punishes herself for drinking alcohol. Baby taunts Pravina for misjudging Meenakshi.
Pravina and Leela makes fun of Baa whereas Baa wishes to celebrate Saumil's birthday in her own way secretly.
Saumil tells Arvind about Baa's behavior and Anish apologizes to Baa.
Anish and Thakkar family members play cards.
Pravina taunts Meenakshi for doing household work slow.
Mehul accepts his crime and tells to Baa. Pravina beats Mehul for lying to the family members. Baa apologizes to Gattu for misjudging him.
Pravina tells Leela about her discussion with Baa about Anish. Narsi kaka overhears their conversation and informs to Baa.
Arvind gets tensed to know that his boss is plotting with the bank employees against him.
The Thakkar family is shocked to know about Arvind and his boss's conspiracy against him.
Harshad is surprised to see Arvind in his house. Arvind tries to convince Harshad to keep his money with himself and not try to help since he is no longer part of the family.
Subodh and Praveen plan to collect money for Ganesh Pooja. Pravina and Leela are shocked to meet Gomati.

Harshad visits the Thakar house and tries to convince Baa to let him participate in the bidding. The Thakkar family support Harshad, but Baa starts bidding against Harshad to oust him of the Thakkar house and Arvind tries to support her.
Praveen takes Harshad's bidding money by lying to Baa and tries to convince the family members about keeping the money, but they refuses to support him.
Gattu and children encourage Baby as they notice her trying to walk without support. Arvind informs Baa about Dimple's marriage proposal.
Baa enjoys on seeing Praveena, Leela and Meenakshi bidding to see if Charubala says Tushhar 10 times within 4 minutes. Baa apologizes to Baby for being careless about her polio drops.

Praveen fall in the well while he traduces Meenakshi against Baa. Tushar cracks idiotic jokes in front of Baa, Leela and Praveena because of which they don't listen to Gattu who wants to inform them about Praveen.
Baa keeps a bet with Praveen that she will start water supply within half an hour failing which she would jump into the well or he would be thrown into the well again.
Charubala challenges Leela, Praveena and Meenakshi that Baby will agree for marrying Kamlesh. Kamlesh and Baby share feelings with each other.

Anish tries to convince Baa about Baby. Baby is happy as Baa supports her decision not to marry Kamlesh. Praveena gets tensed for not finding her children in the house and then Gattu informs her that the schoolbus is filled with water and floating on the road.

The children enjoy in Harshad's house. Praveena is tensed as Praveen informs her that he is trapped in a manhole and will surely die after which the phone cuts abruptly. Harshad consoles Praveena when she weeps inconsolably.
Praveena breaks down when Gattu tells that Praveen is dead bluntly. Baby and Dimple become happy as Gattu informs them that Anish has sent "Navratri" passes for the family.

Leela tries to convince Praveena to support her for Dimple, but she refuses. Praveena gets tensed to see that Baby is dreaming about Anish whereas Anish and Dimple love each other. The Thakkar family enjoys "Navratri" Garba party.
Anish and Dimple win first prize in Garba competition and Anish following the lead from Subodh announces that he loves Dimple. Baby gets upset to hear that Anish loves Dimple.
Anish and Dimple come to know that Baby loves Anish from Gattu. He apologizes to Baby for misleading her. Baby tries to convince Dimple and Anish to love each other.

Arvind gets furious on family members after knowing about Dimple and Anish. They try to convince him to discuss with Baa about Dimple's marriage with Anish which he refuses vehemently. Baa gets tensed when she comes to know that Dimple loves Anish from Praveena.

data: "I'm Naru! I'll Be~come the Manager!" "Watashi wa Naru! Tenchou ni Na~ru!" (私はなる！店長にな〜る！)

Rinne, a messenger from the Prism World, is heading to a world in need of the Prism's sparkle, alongside her Pair Friend, when a mysterious accident occurs. 14-year-old Naru Ayase, a girl who has the ability to see the colors of music, applies to become the manager of a new fashion store known as "Prism Stone". At the Prism Show examination, Naru is unable to jump a Prism Jump, but performs a brand new type of Prism Show, known as a Prism Live, with the help of the penguin-like Pair Friend, Lovelyn. During Naru's performance, an enigmatic girl takes the stage and successfully jumps 4 consecutive Prism Jumps! The girl disappears soon after, leaving Naru mystified, but manages to get the position of Prism Stone's manager!

The girl disappears soon after, leaving Naru mystified, but manages to get the position of Prism Stone's manager!
"Leave it to Ann! Pop'n Sweets!" "Ann ni Omakase! Poppun Suiitsu!" (あんにお任せ！ポップンスイーツ！)

Naru is tasked with creating desserts for Prism Stone's sweets corner. Another one of Prism Stone's employees, DJ Coo, suggests she go to the sweets buffet to find inspiration. There, Naru runs into her classmate, Ann Fukuhara, who is skilled in the art of making sweets and dreams of becoming a patisserie, despite her father's protests. On her way home, Ann meets another Pair Friend, Poppun, and takes him home with her. However, Poppun is scared away by Ann's father and flies off. Ann follows him, leading her to Prism Stone, where Naru is unsuccessfully attempting to make sweets. Ann gives her a hand, and is eventually offered to work at "Prism Stone"'s sweets corner, but must be able to perform a Prism Show. At her Prism Show examination, Ann performs a Prism Live with the help of Poppun, in addition to two consecutive Prism Jumps. After Ann's performance, the mysterious girl from before appears, introducing herself as the amnesiac Rinne.

"Cross is Ito? COOL & HOT" "Kurosu ga Ito? KUURU ANDO HOTTO" (クロスがいと？ COOL & HOT)

Naru is tasked with finding someone to be in charge of Prism Stone's makeup corner. Meanwhile, at Edel Rose, an academy for elite Prism Stars, Bell Renjouji, one of the applicants for Prism Stone's manager position, ponders Rinne's ability to do four consecutive Prism Jumps, something only Prism Star June Amou could do until recently. After seeing her classmate Ito "Cross" Suzuno's makeup, Naru asks for Ito to work at Prism Stone. Ito at first refuses, but is convinced by Lovelyn, Poppun, and Ito's own Pair Friend, Coolun. At her Prism Show examination, Ito performs a Prism Live with the help of Coolun, in addition to two consecutive Prism Jumps.

"Welcome to the Prism Stone Easter!" "Purizumu Sutoon Iisutaa ni Youkoso!" (プリズムストーン イースターにようこそ！)

After learning that rival fashion store Dear Crown is holding an Easter event, Naru and the others decide to hold their own Easter at Prism Stone the same day as Dear Crown's in order to bring in more customers. However, Naru is unable to come up with something special to do at the event, but finds inspiration with the help of Rinne. On the day of the Easter event, Naru performs a Prism Show, but like before, is unable to do a Prism Jump. Rinne once again joins Naru on stage, and they perform a dual Prism Live, in which Rinne executes her four consecutive Prism Jumps, shocking Bell and her companions, Wakana Morizono and Otoha Takanashi, who came to watch Naru's Prism Show. With their first event a success, the Prism Stone team celebrates, with Ito finally letting Naru and Ann call her by her true name, rather than "Cross".

"My Song is a Multi♡Colored~ream" "Watashi no Uta wa Iro♡Toridoriimu" (私の歌は色♡トリドリーム)

As Prism Stone is gaining more customers, the store's owner, Chisato Ibara, feels that it's time for a new Prism Show. Chisato explains that Prism Shows are generally performed with a Prism Star's own song, known as a "My Song", and tasks Naru with having a My Song by Saturday. Naru has trouble coming up with a My Song, and enlists the help of a boy who she hears singing on an apartment rooftop every time she comes home from school. However, the boy refuses, saying he isn't going to give his songs to anyone. The boy, Kouji Mihama, is explained to be a former student of Edel Rose, but quit after his song was stolen by another student named Hiro. Naru goes to apologize to Kouji and manages to convey to him that his song made her happy, while he believed otherwise. Kouji agrees to write her a song, but only on one condition - Naru can never tell anyone he was the one to write it. On the day of Naru's My Song debut, Naru receives the song from Kouji, and upon hearing it, comes up with the song's choreography. She soon goes to perform, successfully pulling off her first Prism Jump alongside her Prism Live.

"The Cool Heart Beats with Heat!" "Kuuru na Haato ga Biito de Hiito!" (クールなハートがビートでヒート！)

Chisato announces that the Prism Stone team is going on a tour, with the first stop being the all-boys school Kakkyouin Academy. Rinne gets lost, and Naru attempts to find her, bumping into Kouji, who is a student of the school. Naru also meets Hiro Hayami, unbeknowst to her Hiro is the one who stole Kouji's song and is using the song for his Prism Star debut. Naru and Kouji soon meet up with Ann, Ito, and Chisato. Due to her crush on Kouji and jealousy over Naru and Kouji's relationship, Ito decides she will be the one to perform a Prism Show rather than Naru, debuting with her My Song. Rinne soon returns to the others, having won the Miss Kakkyouin contest.

Naru also meets Hiro Hayami, unbeknowst to her Hiro is the one who stole Kouji's song and is using the song for his Prism Star debut. Naru and Kouji soon meet up with Ann, Ito, and Chisato. Due to her crush on Kouji and jealousy over Naru and Kouji's relationship, Ito decides she will be the one to perform a Prism Show rather than Naru, debuting with her My Song. Rinne soon returns to the others, having won the Miss Kakkyouin contest.

"Sweet Magic for a Sour Dad" "Ganko Oyaji ni Suiito Majikku" (がンコ親父にスイートマジック)

Chisato asks the girls to invite their parents over to Prism Stone for formal greetings, deciding that the meeting will coincide with Ann's My Song debut. Naru creates invitations and delivers them to Ann and Ito's parents, but unbeknownst to her, Ann and Ito are not on very good terms with their fathers. Ann has not yet told her father about her job, knowing fully well he would attempt to force her to quit. After Ann's father learns from Naru that Ann is making sweets at Prism Stone, he kicks Ann out of the house. Ann, along with Rinne, stays at Naru's house for the night, where Rinne comes up with a new design for Ann using the dress Ann wore for her very Prism Show. Ann wears the design for her My Song debut, and her father, reminded of Ann's first Prism Show, agrees to let her continue working at Prism Stone.

"The Boys' Bout is a Dance Battle" "Otoko no Shoubu wa Dansu Batoru" (男の勝負はダンスバトル)

Wakana accuses Ann of stealing her My Song, with Bell explaining that Wakana has been singing that song at Prism Shows for a long time now. Ann says that the song was written by an upperclassman of hers, Kazuki Nishina, and given to her when he graduated. In order to prove her claims, Ann is asked by Coo to bring Kazuki to Prism Stone the next day. Naru, Ann, and Ito meet up with Kazuki, who says that the one to write the song was not him, but Kouji, who had given it to him when Kouji dropped out of Edel Rose. Hiro, Bell, Wakana, and Otoha meet up with the Prism Stone team, with Hiro revealing that Kouji was supposed to debut with him, but "chickened out", according to Wakana. After Hiro begins mocking Kouji, Kazuki challenges him to a dance battle - if Kazuki were to win, the song will belong to Ann. Before the dance battle begins, Kazuki saves a little boy from being hit by a truck, causing him sprain his ankle. Due to his injury, Hiro wins the dance battle. However, Kouji arrives, saying he gave the song to Kazuki, allowing Ann to continue using the song as her My Song. Note: This is the first episode in any Pretty Rhythm series to have a male character's Prism Show be CG animated

In order to confirm whether or not Rinne can actually do four consecutive Prism Jumps, Bell, Wakana, and Otoha invite Prism Stone to an Edel Rose Prism Show. However, Chisato says Rinne can't go due to urgent business. Due to this, Prism Stone cannot perform at Edel Rose, as all four members aren't there. Ann decides to call Rinne, but learns from Chisato that Rinne has disappeared - as she is already at Edel Rose, as discovered by Naru. Naru and Ann go after Rinne, but can't find her. Ito finds out about the plan concerning Rinne after an impulsive outburst from Otoha, and tells Naru and Ann. Ann and Wakana decide to hold a Prism Show contest in which the loser must quit Prism Shows for good. Fortunately, a rainstorm occurs before the contest begin. The six girls then see Rinne dancing in the rain, singing her My Song. She performs her first solo Prism Live and executes her consecutive jumps, confirming that the four jumps are no magic trick. The Prism Stone girls learn that Bell, Wakana, and Otoha are preparing for the Dreaming Session, an upcoming Prism Show tournament, in which they decide to enter themselves. Note: The Prism Mates cameo as performing Prism Stars from Edel Rose

For pilots:
table-1339-190.caption: Definition of V MC(A)
data: FAR and EASA/CS 23 and 25 §149 and equivalent present the definition of V MC (is V MCA ) for the design and certification of multi-engine airplanes: Minimum Control speed is the minimum flight speed at which the airplane is controllable with a bank angle of not more than 5° when the critical engine suddenly becomes inoperative and the remaining engine is operating at takeoff power. This definition is correct for tail design engineers and for certification but is often inappropriately copied into pilot manuals, because it contains elements that are neither appropriate, nor applicable to operational pilots.

Once the airplane is designed and built, the selected tail size imposes control limitations on, i.e. conditions to, pilots. The V MC(A) definition for use by pilots is therefore different than the V MC(A) definition for tail design engineers and for certification, and could be: V MC(A) is the minimum speed for maintaining steady straight flight only when an engine fails or is inoperative and with the corresponding opposite engine set to provide maximum thrust, provided a bank angle is being maintained of (3° – ) 5° away from the inoperative engine and the rudder is used up to maximum to maintain straight flight. The exact required bank angle (also used to size the vertical tail) is to be provided by the airplane manufacturer with the V MC data. In addition, the manufacturer should specify the configuration (flaps, etc.) for which this, and other published V MC 's is/ are valid. It is important to notice that V MC(A) is defined and determined for steady straight flight only, while banking a few degrees away from the inoperative engine.

title: ICECLAY
Highly efficient production of ultra-lightweight clay-aerogel materials and their integrated composites for building insulation
table-1339-253.caption: External links
data: The ICECLAY project aims at creating a new generation of low cost and most efficient insulation materials for EU building construction and hence enhancing the competitiveness of SMEs in EU construction sector. The ICECLAY will provide, due to their extremely porous structure and reduced thickness, the superior thermal insulation specially designed for highly energy efficiency building’s retrofit and advanced HAVC systems. The developed innovative thin and flexible lightweight ICECLAY board and film will claim to be an excellent and cheaper alternative to the unaffordable high-performance insulation materials like the space oriented supercritical-dried silica aerogel and vacuum insulation panels. The developed powder based ICECLAY will be used as superior enhancing thermal insulation fillers for a broad range of building products like concrete, drywalls, bricks, plasters and coatings.
